The paper deals with the problem of group testing, which is a well-studied problem in computer science and information theory. The use of randomized algorithms and the analysis of their performance is a common theme in many sub-fields of computer science, including information theory (cs.IT), data structures (cs.DS), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), machine learning (cs.LG), and social and information networks (cs.SI). Given that the paper focuses on the design and analysis of a randomized algorithm for group testing, these sub-categories are the most likely candidates.
